('spanish:5-2-festivals-and-traditions:mcq:0eff57e9', 'spanish', 'spanish:5-2-festivals-and-traditions', '5.2 Festivals and Traditions', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Complete: ‘Este año, los niños ___ de superhéroes para el carnaval.’", "options": ["se disfrazan", "disfrazan", "se disfrazaron", "se disfrazaban"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "disfrazarse is reflexive, present tense → se disfrazan. B drops ‘se’, C is preterite, D is imperfect."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:5-2-festivals-and-traditions:mcq:bd0e785d', 'spanish', 'spanish:5-2-festivals-and-traditions', '5.2 Festivals and Traditions', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "How do you say ‘We ate together and danced all night’?", "options": ["Comimos juntos y bailamos toda la noche.", "Comemos juntos y bailamos toda la noche.", "Comíamos juntos y bailábamos toda la noche.", "Vamos a comer juntos y a bailar toda la noche."]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "A completed one-off past event needs the preterite: comimos, bailamos. B is present, C is imperfect (used to), D is a future plan."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:5-2-festivals-and-traditions:tf:d248eb41', 'spanish', 'spanish:5-2-festivals-and-traditions', '5.2 Festivals and Traditions', 'tf', 'tf', 1, '{"question": "‘Los Reyes Magos’ is celebrated on 6th January."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": true, "explain": "6 January — Epiphany, when the Three Kings bring presents in Spain."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:5-2-festivals-and-traditions:tf:ff921a3a', 'spanish', 'spanish:5-2-festivals-and-traditions', '5.2 Festivals and Traditions', 'tf', 'tf', 1, '{"question": "‘La Tomatina’ takes place in Pamplona."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": false, "explain": "La Tomatina is in Buñol; Pamplona hosts San Fermín (the running of the bulls)."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:5-2-festivals-and-traditions:tf:7ac27f17', 'spanish', 'spanish:5-2-festivals-and-traditions', '5.2 Festivals and Traditions', 'tf', 'tf', 1, '{"question": "‘Reunirse’ is reflexive, so ‘the family gets together’ is ‘la familia se reúne’."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": true, "explain": "Reflexive verbs need me/te/se — se reúne."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:5-2-festivals-and-traditions:tf:87450426', 'spanish', 'spanish:5-2-festivals-and-traditions', '5.2 Festivals and Traditions', 'tf', 'tf', 1, '{"question": "The preterite tense is used to describe what usually happens every year."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": false, "explain": "Habitual actions use soler/imperfect; the preterite is for one completed past event."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:5-2-festivals-and-traditions:tf:cb5e7ad7', 'spanish', 'spanish:5-2-festivals-and-traditions', '5.2 Festivals and Traditions', 'tf', 'tf', 1, '{"question": "‘El Día de los Muertos’ is a Mexican celebration."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": true, "explain": "El Día de los Muertos (1–2 November) is celebrated across Mexico."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:5-2-festivals-and-traditions:tf:bfd2887a', 'spanish', 'spanish:5-2-festivals-and-traditions', '5.2 Festivals and Traditions', 'tf', 'tf', 1, '{"question": "‘Lo pasé genial’ means ‘I had a great time’."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": true, "explain": "pasarlo genial/bien = to have a great/good time."}'::jsonb),
